| **Platform Engineer** | Built, Enabled, Standardized | Internal platform + developer experience + golden paths |

## 8. Format Rules (NEVER CHANGE)

- **Page:** Single page, US Letter (216 × 279 mm)
- **Font:** Calibri throughout
- **Body size:** 10pt (size 20 in half-points)
- **Skills & contact size:** 10pt (size 20)
- **Project tech stack:** 9.5pt italic dark gray
- **Name:** 16pt bold, centered
- **Section headers:** 11pt bold with accent underline
- **Margins:** 25pt top + 25pt bottom, 0.5" left/right
- **Color schemes:**
  - **Teal `#1A7A7A` + gold `#C8A951`** — startup/SaaS roles
  - **Navy `#1B3A6B` + slate gold `#B8942A`** — enterprise/BFSI/Cloud/SRE roles (DEFAULT)
- **Skill row format:** Category name (bold black) + items (regular), each row ONE line at 9.5pt
- **Bullets:** Action verb + context + quantified result; 1-2 lines each; mix bold key terms
- **URLs:** plain text format with hyperlinks underneath (NOT "LinkedIn" / "GitHub" labels)
- **British -ise spelling:** Dockerised, containerised (not -ize)
- **Sections (in order):** Header → Summary (3 lines max) → Technical Skills (8 rows) → Professional Experience → Key Projects → Education → Achievements
- **Education and Achievements:** ALWAYS separate sections
- **"Immediate joiner":** Only include if JD explicitly asks
- **Certifications:** Default = omit. Include only if JD asks.
